cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this benchmark or build on its results, please cite it as below."
title: "Bonsai vs Qwen3.5 on Edge: Benchmarking Aggressively Quantized LLMs on NVIDIA Jetson Orin"
abstract: >
  A practical benchmark comparing the Bonsai 1-bit LLM, the Ternary-Bonsai
  mlx-2bit family (1.7B / 4B / 8B), and seven Qwen3.5 variants (0.8B–35B)
  on an NVIDIA Jetson Orin. Covers accuracy across 98 questions in 7
  categories (general knowledge, math, coding, history, logical reasoning,
  language understanding, Persian) and throughput (generation and prompt
  tok/s) via llama.cpp and a source-built MLX CUDA backend (sm_87).
